webpackJsonp([0x81b8806e42603000],{"../../../work/landr/packages/landr/node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/index.json":function(e,n){e.exports={data:{repo:{name:"landr",full_name:"resin-io/landr",description:"source code = website üè†",forks_count:1,stargazers_count:6,html_url:"https://github.com/resin-io/landr",releases:[{id:7026841,tag_name:"landr@1.0.2-beta2.1",html_url:"https://github.com/resin-io/landr/releases/tag/landr%401.0.2-beta2.1"}],issues:[{id:247393213,title:"Parsing issues",labels:[]},{id:247340957,title:"Add github type links to markdown",labels:[]},{id:246720496,title:"Etcher example",labels:[]},{id:246043573,title:"Occasionally the cached github response is cleaned up by gatsby.",labels:[]},{id:243406403,title:"Setup a CI to build demo sites",labels:[]},{id:243401234,title:"Features component",labels:[{id:488961047,name:"enhancement"},{id:488961050,name:"question"}]},{id:243396242,title:"Automatically build all pages in `www/src/pages`.",labels:[]},{id:242658287,title:"Add cli option to build from custom directory",labels:[{id:488961047,name:"enhancement"}]},{id:239598492,title:"Pagination on releases?",labels:[]},{id:239129565,title:"Use graphql github api",labels:[]},{id:237852941,title:"Add test command",labels:[{id:488961047,name:"enhancement"}]},{id:237303362,title:"We *could* pass queries as context",labels:[{id:488961050,name:"question"}]},{id:198637120,title:"Add versionist",labels:[{id:488961047,name:"enhancement"}]}],contributors:[{avatar_url:"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/9499917?v=4",login:"craig-mulligan",contributions:102,html_url:"https://github.com/craig-mulligan"},{avatar_url:"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/107844?v=4",login:"tyrantkhan",contributions:1,html_url:"https://github.com/tyrantkhan"}]},readme:{sections:[{title:"How it works",html:"<p>When you run landr on your local repository, it gathers info by leveraging standard conventions.\nIt‚Äôll first look for a git remote from <code>github.com</code> and retrieve some basic information about your project from the github api (<code>contribution stats</code>, <code>releases</code>), it will then parse standard files like <code>README.md</code>, <code>CHANGELOG.md</code>, <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code> &#x26; <code>/docs</code>, it‚Äôll then use the data to build out beautiful pages for your website.</p>\n<p>This allows the maintenance of your website to be a side effect of keeping your software project inline with standard github conventions.</p>"},{title:"How it works",html:"<p>When you run landr on your local repository, it gathers info by leveraging standard conventions.\nIt‚Äôll first look for a git remote from <code>github.com</code> and retrieve some basic information about your project from the github api (<code>contribution stats</code>, <code>releases</code>), it will then parse standard files like <code>README.md</code>, <code>CHANGELOG.md</code>, <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code> &#x26; <code>/docs</code>, it‚Äôll then use the data to build out beautiful pages for your website.</p>\n<p>This allows the maintenance of your website to be a side effect of keeping your software project inline with standard github conventions.</p>"},{title:"Quick start guide",html:'<p>Install:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>npm i -g landr@canary</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>From the root of your local <code>.git</code> repo run:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr develop</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Visit <code>http://localhost:8080</code>.</p>\n<p>Deploy to github pages:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr deploy</code></pre>\n      </div>'},{title:"Site composition",html:"<p>We‚Äôll currently build these pages based on the info we can infer from a repo.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>/</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jumbotron (title + description of project)</li>\n<li>Installation / Getting started</li>\n<li>instructions pulled from <code>README.md</code></li>\n<li>Features</li>\n<li>list of features</li>\n<li>Changelog (Last entry, with link to view more)</li>\n<li>link to <code>/changelog</code></li>\n<li>Contribute</li>\n<li>(Top 5 contributors / order by commits )</li>\n<li>Issue explorer (default tag is <code>help wanted</code>)</li>\n<li>link to <code>/contribute</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>/docs</p>\n<ul>\n<li>generates a page for each /docs/* page.</li>\n<li>Sidebar navigation</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>/changelog</p>\n<ul>\n<li>accordion list view of every entry from <code>changelog.md</code> or fallback to pulling from github releases</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>/contribute</p>\n<ul>\n<li>list of contributors</li>\n<li>stats from github api (health score/languages etc.)</li>\n<li>instructions from <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"},{title:"Customizing",html:'<p>It‚Äôs great to get a full website with out touching any css/html, but you may want personalize the website by editing templates and styles, landr comes with an <code>eject</code> command to customize any piece of the website.</p>\n<h3 id="styles"><a href="#styles" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Styles</h3>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr eject --styles</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>This will write a file to <code>&#x3C;project-root>/www/styles/index.scss</code> where you can customize theme variables and add any custom sass.</p>\n<h3 id="components"><a href="#components" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Components</h3>\n<p>All of landr‚Äôs templates are made from react components, which makes them modular and easy to customize.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr eject --component jumbotron</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Will write a file <code>&#x3C;project-root>/www/components/jumbotron.js</code> you can make any customizations you like.</p>\n<p>The component is a standard <a href="https://facebook.github.io/react/">react.js</a> but you can also export a <a href="http://graphql.org/learn/queries/#fragments">graphql query fragment</a> to customize the data we as react <code>props</code>.</p>\n<p>Heres an example:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>import React from \'react\';\nimport { Banner, Heading, Text, Lead } from \'rebass\';\n\nexport default ({ repo }) => {\n  return (\n    <Banner\n    \tcolor=\'white\'\n    \tbg=\'gray9\'\n      >\n    \t<Heading\n    \t\tf={[ 4, 5, 6, 7 ]}>\n    \t\t{repo.name}\n    \t</Heading>\n      <Lead>\n      \t{repo.description}\n      </Lead>\n    </Banner>\n  );\n};\n\nexport graphql`\n  fragment HeroRepoFragment on Repo {\n    name\n    description\n  }\n`</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id="pages"><a href="#pages" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Pages</h3>\n<p>Most times you‚Äôll only need to update components but if you need you can customise an entire page.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr eject --page index</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id="layouts"><a href="#layouts" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Layouts</h3>\n<p>Sometime‚Äôs you‚Äôll want to change the layout of all the pages. Landr current has to <code>index</code> (default for all pages) and <code>docs</code> the default for an <code>/docs</code> page.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>landr eject --layout index</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3 id="configuration"><a href="#configuration" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Configuration</h3>\n<p>I know, we said there is zero configuration, but there are some cases where configuration is necessary for example if you need to add analytics tokens, or ignore certain files.</p>\n<p>landr allows configuration via a <code>landr.conf.js</code> file in <code>&#x3C;project-root>/www/</code> it must export a config object.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-js"><code><span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">// www/landr.conf.js</span>\nmodule<span class="token punctuation">.</span>exports <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  analytics<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n    mixpanel<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token operator">&lt;</span>mixpanel<span class="token operator">-</span>id<span class="token operator">></span>\n    googleAnalytics<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token operator">&lt;</span>ga<span class="token operator">-</span>id<span class="token operator">></span>\n  <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>'},{title:"Why landr",html:"<p>You have to maintain your source code why maintain a website too?</p>\n<p>As a software company we have a growing number of websites to build and maintain. We built landr so we could focus on our projects and not their websites.</p>"},{title:"Contributing",html:'<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>yarn\n\nyarn run bootstrap\n\nyarn start</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Get to work. üë∑</p>'},{title:"License",html:'<p>Landr is free software, and may be redistributed under the terms specified in the <a href="LICENSE">license</a>.</p>'}]}},pathContext:{title:"Index"}}}});
